=== CONTRACT ===
For every HTML file in .claude-project/nestfind/design/html/*.html there MUST be
exactly one YAML file in .claude-project/nestfind/user_stories/<basename>.yaml
with the same basename. No more, no fewer.

Each YAML MUST carry multiple scenario buckets. At minimum:
  - acceptance_criteria: 2+ entries (happy-path actions on this page)
  - boundary_cases:      1+ entry  (min/max/empty/whitespace/overflow)
  - error_scenarios:     1+ entry  (401/403/404/500, network failure, validation error)
  - state_transitions:   1+ entry  (loading / empty / error UI state)
Total scenarios across buckets: >= 5.

=== INPUTS YOU CAN READ ===
- .claude-project/nestfind/design/html/*.html        (source of truth for page count)
- .claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_KNOWLEDGE.md (features + roles)
- .claude-project/nestfind/docs/PROJECT_API.md       (endpoints each page calls)
- .claude-project/nestfind/user_stories/_fixtures.yaml (credentials + seed data)
- existing .claude-project/nestfind/user_stories/*.yaml (may be bundled legacy YAMLs)

=== ALGORITHM ===

STEP 1 — inventory
  Glob '.claude-project/nestfind/design/html/*.html'. Record basename list.
  Glob '.claude-project/nestfind/user_stories/*.yaml' (exclude _fixtures, _index).
  For each HTML basename, decide:
    a) matching YAML exists with >=5 scenarios and all 4 buckets → SKIP
    b) matching YAML exists but shallow (<5 scenarios or missing buckets) → DEEPEN
    c) no matching YAML → CREATE

STEP 2 — legacy bundle split (one-time migration)
  Legacy bundle YAMLs (feature-level, covering multiple pages) exist:
    auth.yaml, worker-service-application.yaml, worker-application-tracking.yaml,
    payment-refund.yaml, document-management.yaml, company-dashboard.yaml,
    company-manager-management.yaml, admin-operations.yaml, admin-permissions.yaml,
    i18n-responsive.yaml, notifications.yaml
  For each bundle:
    - Identify which HTML pages it actually covers (by matching acceptance_criteria
      ui_route / endpoint to PROJECT_API routes → map back to HTML filename).
    - Copy each acceptance_criterion, boundary_case, error_scenario into the
      corresponding per-page YAML.
    - When the bundle has been fully redistributed, delete it. Otherwise leave
      it as a cross-page "feature narrative" reference (keep role, feature,
      goal — drop ACs that were moved).

STEP 3 — CREATE / DEEPEN per HTML page
  Open the HTML file. Parse (via Read — do not launch a headless browser):
    - forms, inputs, selects, textareas → validation scenarios
    - buttons (submit, delete, cancel) → action ACs
    - tables, lists → empty-state + loading-state
    - tabs, modals, filters → state transitions
    - error / empty / "no data" slots → state_transitions bucket
    - role-gated badges or copy ("admin only", etc.) → auth error_scenario

  Cross-reference PROJECT_API.md for endpoints the page hits.
  Cross-reference _fixtures.yaml to pick the right role/credentials.

  Write YAML with this shape:

  ```yaml
  id: US-<page-basename-upper>
  role: <worker|company_manager|admin|all>   # from URL prefix (b-=worker, company-=company_manager, admin-=admin, others=all)
  feature: <one-sentence label>
  page: <basename>.html
  goal: |
    As a <role> on the <page label> page I can ... so that ...

  acceptance_criteria:
    - id: AC-1
      description: <happy path action>
      ui_route: <path>
      endpoint: <METHOD /api/path or "none">
      expected: <status + UI assertion>
    - id: AC-2
      ...

  boundary_cases:
    - case: <min/max/empty/whitespace/overflow scenario + expected outcome>

  error_scenarios:
    - scenario: <401/403/404/500 or network failure + expected UI>

  state_transitions:
    - state: loading
      expected: <skeleton / spinner / disabled button>
    - state: empty
      expected: <empty-state component text + CTA>
    - state: error
      expected: <inline error + retry CTA>

  fixture_refs:
    - users.<key>
  ```

  Set scenarios_total = sum across all four buckets. Must be >= 5.

STEP 4 — update _index.yaml
  Rewrite _index.yaml listing every final per-page YAML:
    ```
    generated: <ISO timestamp>
    source: per-HTML-page authorship (one yaml per design/html/*.html)
    project: nestfind
    page_parity_generated: true
    html_count: <N>
    yaml_count: <N>
    stories:
      - file: <basename>.yaml
        page: <basename>.html
        role: <role>
        feature: <feature label>
        scenarios_total: <int>
        buckets:
          acceptance_criteria: <int>
          boundary_cases: <int>
          error_scenarios: <int>
          state_transitions: <int>
    ```

  The "page_parity_generated: true" line is required for verification.

=== RULES ===
- One YAML per HTML page. No bundles (legacy bundles either get
  split or retired).
- Do NOT modify _fixtures.yaml.
- Do NOT touch HTML files.
- Do NOT invent endpoints not in PROJECT_API.md.
- If a page is public (login, landing, signup, verify-email), role = all and
  auth-error scenarios focus on form validation, not 401/403.
- Keep goal/description text concrete — no "user should be able to …" fluff.



